  "text": "with 1 y\u223cx being the independent r.v. of the indicator function that y formed an edge with x , one gets by a well known theorem in probability theory for t \u2212 \u03c4 large a limiting Poisson distribution with expectation equal to E (d in (x, t)) (see [CITATION_1] for recent sharp results in this direction). In complete analogy to section 2 we obtain after integration over \u03c9 a scale free distribution for \u03c8 (k, \u03c4, t)-the not on \u03c9 conditioned indegree distribution. Taking explicit care on the \u03c4 dependence we get",
